\c 33
\q1
\v 1 Shout with joy in YHWH, O righteous ones,
\q1 For the upright praise is becoming.\f + Cf. Pss 15 and 24.\f*
\q1
\v 2 Praise YHWH with the lyre,
\q1 With the ten-stringed harp praise him.
\q1
\v 3 Sing to him a new song,
\q1 Play skillfully on the strings with a shout of joy.
\q1
\v 4 For the word of YHWH is upright,
\q1 And his every work is in faithfulness.\f + Cf. Pss 15 and 24.\f*
\q1
\v 5 He loves righteousness and justice,
\q1 The steadfast love of YHWH has filled the earth.
\q1
\v 6 By the word of YHWH the heavens were made,
\q1 And by the breath of his mouth all their host.
\q1
\v 7 He gathered the waters of the sea like a dam,
\q1 He put the deeps in storehouses.
\q1
\v 8 Let all the earth fear YHWH,
\q1 Let all the inhabitants of the earth be afraid of him.\f + Ps 24:1-2.\f*
\q1
\v 9 For he spoke, and it was,
\q1 He commanded and it stood.
\q1
\v 10 YHWH destroys the counsel of the nations,
\q1 He thwarts the plans of the peoples.\f + Ps 2.\f*
\q1
\v 11 The counsel of YHWH will stand forever,
\q1 The plans of his heart generation by generation.
\q1
\v 12 Blessed is the nation whose God is YHWH,
\q1 The people he chose as his heritage.
\q1
\v 13 From heaven YHWH looks,
\q1 He sees all the sons of man.
\q1
\v 14 From the abode where he sits he gazes,
\q1 To all the inhabitants of the earth.
\q1
\v 15 The one who fashions together their heart,
\q1 Who notices all their deeds.
\q1
\v 16 There is no king saved by the greatness of his army,
\q1 A hero is not saved by the greatness of his strength.
\q1
\v 17 The horse is a deception for deliverance,
\q1 And in the greatness of its power it will not save.
\q1
\v 18 Behold the eye of YHWH is to those who fear him,
\q1 To those who hope in his steadfast love.
\q1
\v 19 To rescue their soul from death,
\q1 And to preserve them in famine.
\q1
\v 20 Our soul waits for YHWH,
\q1 He is our help and our shield.
\q1
\v 21 For in him our heart is glad,
\q1 For in his holy name we trust.
\q1
\v 22 Let your steadfast love be on us, O YHWH,
\q1 As we hope in you.